{
  "title": "Platform Earth Roadmap",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "484d7e7a1ae4d34f",
      "text": "The roadmap for [[platform earth]] is a living document governed by it's members. We are seeking to build a [[microservice]] [[platform for the commons]], based on open source software, and a pragmatic, agile approach to software development."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "d8118d020acfcc0e",
      "text": "We seek to combine modern software strategies, being widely deployed in large companies, to solve the problem of multiple teams working on [[complex software projects]], with fully decentralised [[autonomous groups]] collaborating across international borders to provide [[equitable working practices]], in a way that is compatible with our [[ecosystem]] on this planet."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "c54ecfcaed4bd3ef",
      "text": "To this end, we aim to build upon the extensive history of the [[cooperative movement]], and not-for profit sector, while curating the best available tools and practices, that are emerging from the [[decentralised web]] and privacy preserving [[distributed ledger]] (ie blockchain) based technologies founded on an [[agent-centric]] or [[self-sovereign]] model of identity.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "0ea6586db9c17d8f",
      "text": "These tools and practices include:"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "e510aed0c9d77a16",
      "text": "- [[Continuous Deployment]]\n- [[Microservices]]\n- [[Docker based deployment]]\n- [[Agile Project Management]]\n- [[Participatory Design]]\n- [[Decentralised Technology]]\n- [[Blockchain]] and [[DLT]]\n- [[Viable system model]] and [[Cooperative Governance]]"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "a696784f998ee208",
      "text": "There is a lot of terminology here - technical and organisational. This is unavoidable at this stage, as we are building on the work of others. However we must emphasise that our aim is to integrate these technologies using simple [[pragmatix]], and a social community driven process in which we build what is needed, and communicate in the language of the stakeholders we are designing for."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "f3c644ee025f6ac4",
      "text": "To this end we are prioritising the following components for the first release of [[Platform Earth]]:"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "080a5d5491c40e66",
      "text": "- [[Microservices for Governance]]. Building on top of [[OneClickOrgs]] we will create a series of microservices, and [[Decoupled UI Components]] to enable governance of [[Cooperative Federation]]s."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "9ecbcc9b6a88020d",
      "text": "- [[Microservices for Trading]]. [[Ecommony]] is our microservice platform for [[Mutual Credit]] and [[Hard Currency]] trading between cooperatives. The software will be based on the [[Credit Commons API]] and will use a [[blockchain]] based [[distributed ledger]]."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "83f0eaee2e3927bc",
      "text": "- [[Commons World]]. Commons World is a federated knowledge base of technical, cooperative, and commons based knowledge. It is based on top of [[Ward Cunningham]]'s [[Federated Wiki]] project, and enables [[Knowledge Objects]] to be forked and repurposed to the context of participating organisations. It is the basis of our [[Learning Model]] for the [[Cooperative Economy]]."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "9f4c2de150f18353",
      "text": "- [[Static Site Generation]]. Building on top of the above tools, we will provide a suite of microservices that enable content from the commons to be customised, and deployed in an organisational context as robust, highly available static sites. This service will be available to cooperative members in return for [[mutual credit]], facilitating free-as-in-beer deployment of modern sites for events, project, joint ventures, and new cooperatives."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "ad7c8fd35eb48207",
      "text": "The above suite of tools will be made available as a single [[docker]], that can be easily deployed to the cloud or run locally as a [[Decentralised Application]]. because fo the design of the software any organisation running the application on behalf of it's members will be able to share knowledge, and trade with other members of the federation in a variety of ways."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "e7f957cd25bcbb48",
      "text": "We will provide [[One Click Deployment]] of this suite of tools, together with the necessary financial, and governance tools to enable existing organisations, or new cooperative ventures being formed to utilise their own domains, and ownership of their own data, while participating in the commons."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "68a7c7c7aceefe8d",
      "text": "# Incentivised Coproduction\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "3a8361d9852ce66a",
      "text": "The initial product release of [[Platform Earth]] will enable federations of cooperatives to engage in a process of [[Rapid Incentivised Coproduction]] of services for the commons.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "707fe51c756b5ec3",
      "text": "Using [[blockchain]] technology, wedded to clear cooperative legal governance, and a core set of products and services to generate revenue, we will be able to provide the incentive structures required to maintain the develop the technical services the platform requires.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "a12d8f67b8ad6d90",
      "text": "We anticipate following this initial [[Bootstrapping Phase]] with an increasing number of general purpose [[microservices]] that make the job of creating new digital and non-digital services across the cooperative sector simpler and cheaper to produce through leveraging the power of [[Coproduction]] and [[Economies of Scale]] across the sector."
    }
